snippet.textDisplay:
Yeah valorant demand 2.0 TPM, meanwhile cheat developers happy who know about tpm 2.0 security exploits to get into the system encryption on physical level where no anticheat will see any cheat or anything and will trust it as it system component.
The TPM will not save PC from anything. It will only give headache to user if TPM module will fail and user will need to say his OS "goodbye" cause without encryption keys on TPM it will not boot. And even to update bios on your machine or reinstall windows you need firstly to disable secure boot, cause otherwise it won't let you.
They want to secure machines with the flawed tech which is vulnerable already for past few years? Yeah, sure.
snippet.textOriginal:
Yeah valorant demand 2.0 TPM, meanwhile cheat developers happy who know about tpm 2.0 security exploits to get into the system encryption on physical level where no anticheat will see any cheat or anything and will trust it as it system component.
The TPM will not save PC from anything. It will only give headache to user if TPM module will fail and user will need to say his OS "goodbye" cause without encryption keys on TPM it will not boot. And even to update bios on your machine or reinstall windows you need firstly to disable secure boot, cause otherwise it won't let you.
They want to secure machines with the flawed tech which is vulnerable already for past few years? Yeah, sure.
